<br>
However, at 58, I have now completely run dry of soloing and would rather quit the game than solo one more day.  Maybe you hit your wall sooner.  That is possible.  Are the bane spells great?  No doubt.  But it is laughable to think they had anything to do with class balance.  Of course, Verant would say that they aren't class balance related.  To which my answer is, &quot;Well?  WHAT IS!?!?!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/01 11:57:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ur kidding right Verant</span><hr size=1> bane spells great??? um, NO, they are ok at best, yeah they cause good dmg, but damage we should be dealing out at lvl 55 WITHOUT the 2 peridot cast, although at lvl 55 without reagents it should be able to be partial resistable. these spells still do nothing more than make us wanted for raids NOT xp groups, the giant one could make us wanted for xp grps in kael but you still have to obtain lvl 60, which is a major pain in the ass when u shout for hours in a grp and just get responses that you arent good for anything but tl's and ports<br>
